      "post_id" : 55969072,
      "comment_id" : 106426642,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Key here is to exclude /bin/java"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14172284,
      "reputation" : 3376,
      "user_id" : 10238539,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/DpegG.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "MJ Montes",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10238539/mj-montes"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1556883509,
    "creation_date" : 1556883509,
    "answer_id" : 55969072,
    "question_id" : 22307516,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my Ubuntu, I have a headache for 2 days on this issue.</p>\n\n<p>Step 1. Type on the terminal <code>whereis java</code>\nthen it will display something like this</p>\n\n<pre><code>java: /usr/bin/java /etc/java /usr/share/java /usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64/bin/java /usr/share/man/man1/java.1.gz\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Step 2. Take note of the path: \n <code>/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64/bin/java</code></p>\n\n<p>exclude the <code>bin/java</code></p>\n\n<p>your JAVA_HOME = <code>/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
