    "last_activity_date" : 1729450583,
    "creation_date" : 1729450583,
    "answer_id" : 79107834,
    "question_id" : 22307516,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Im building a flutter project within Android Studio, and encountered this gradle build error.</p>\n<p>I had incorrectly set flutter config to the old JDK download directory!</p>\n<p>To check if you have set this variable, run <code>flutter doctor -v</code>, then look for the line <code>Java binary at: </code> under <code>Android Toolchain</code> section.</p>\n<p>To change the setting, first set <code>$JAVA_HOME</code>, then run this command within your flutter project:</p>\n<p><code>flutter config --jdk-dir=&quot;$JAVA_HOME&quot;</code></p>\n<p>Then re-run <code>flutter doctor -v</code> - and reopen your IDE to load the new project config.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 22857031,
      "reputation" : 136,
      "user_id" : 17001732,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/704dd0b0dabaab0ca97ba753d241fc2d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Semerkosa",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/17001732/semerkosa"
